item.title: CVE-2021-4236|2024-08-03T17:23:10.220Z -- github.com%2Fecnepsnai%2Fweb -- github.com%2Fecnepsnai%2Fweb
item.description: Web Sockets do not execute any AuthenticateMethod methods which may be set, leading to a nil pointer dereference if the returned UserData pointer is assumed to be non-nil, or authentication bypass. This issue only affects WebSockets with an AuthenticateMethod hook. Request handlers that do not explicitly use WebSockets are not vulnerable.
